</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Senior Czech police and interior ministry officials said yesterday there was
no evidence of a plot to kill Czech president Vaclav Havel, writes Patrick
Blum in Prague. This contradicted a statement on Thursday by Mr Jan Ruml,
the interior minister, who said police had uncovered a foreign conspiracy to
kill Mr Havel.
