<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAY 93 / Perez threatens to resign
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CARACAS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Venezuela's president, Mr Carlos Andres Perez, has said he will resign if
the country's Supreme Court rules that he should be impeached for allegedly
mishandling Dollars 17m in government funds, writes Joseph Mann in Caracas.
The president's decision came after an unfavourable opinion on his case
written by the chief justice of the Supreme Court was leaked to the press on
May 5.
</TEXT>
