FT  08 MAY 93 / Finn economy shrinks by 0.5%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Finnish economy will shrink by 0.5 per cent this year, its third
consecutive year of negative growth, the country's finance ministry said
yesterday, writes Christopher Brown-Humes in Stockholm.
Its forecast came as the Finnish central bank cut its base rate by half a
percentage point to 7.0 per cent.
