<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 93 / Havel death plot uncovered
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK BLUM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AN assassination plot against Czech president Vaclav Havel was uncovered
yesterday and five of the alleged plotters were arrested, Mr Jan Ruml, the
Czech interior minister, said last night.
Mr Ruml said police had identified seven suspects, all foreigners. The five
who were detained will be held in custody for 30 days while investigations
were carried out.
He said the police had intercepted an anonymous letter threatening Mr
Havel's assassination. Several clues in the letter led to the arrests and
the discovery of weapons.
The nationality of the would-be assassins was not disclosed, but several
commentators suggested a possible link with the Bosnian crisis. Last month
Mr Havel on a visit to Washington denounced Serb atrocities in Bosnia and
compared the West's cautious approach towards Serbia with western
appeasement of Hitler in the 1930s.
