to become chief financial officer of International Business Machines.
Mr Valade, 50, has been Chrysler's vice-president for corporate personnel
since last September and before that was corporate controller of the group.
Most of his career has been in controller's office functions.
He becomes an executive vice-president of Chrysler and joins the office of
the chairman, an inner circle which advises Mr Robert Eaton, the chairman.
