<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 93 / Argentaria offer given enthusiastic reception
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TOM BURNS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ARGENTARIA, Spain's state-owned banking group, yesterday said the public
issue of 25 per cent of its shares to raise Pta120bn (Pounds 687m) had
closed heavily oversubscribed.
International investors subscribed for 10.6 times the shares on offer.
The oversubscription comes as the peseta is under pressure and when
potential political instability is forecast in Spain ahead of the June 6
general election.
Argentaria is placing only 39 per cent (Pta41.8bn) of the total 25 per cent
equity offering outside Spain but international demand for the banking
group's paper totalled Pta445bn - slightly less than the Pta476bn at which
the offer values the whole group.
In Spain, where 61 per cent of the offering will be placed, domestic
institutions and retail investors oversubscribed by 4.6 times. Demand in the
retail tranche totalled Pta206bn against the Pta55.1bn offered.
More than 370,000 small domestic investors applied for paper, which gives
Argentaria the biggest share register of any Spanish banking institution.
Argentaria shares will start trading in Madrid, New York and London on May
12. Analysts believe that a big proportion of the domestically held equity
could eventually end up abroad.
The issue has been globally co-ordinated by Morgan Stanley.
</TEXT>
