such big-time players (Margaret Thatcher, Lord King, Robert Horton)
perform.' Surely he is familiar with the words usually ascribed to the late
Bill Shankly, sometime of Liverpool Football Club: 'Some people think that
football is a matter of life and death - but it's much more important than
that'?
James Fairbairn,
