<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAY 93 / Christie's to auction Michelangelo drawing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONY THORNCROFT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CHRISTIE'S IN London is offering for sale on July 6 two exceptional master
works, both created in the early 1530s, and expected to set auction records
for an Old Master drawing and for a miniature.
The drawing, 'Rest on the flight into Egypt', is by Michelangelo and could
exceed the record Pounds 3.5m paid at Christie's in 1984 for Raphael's
'Study of a man's head and hand'. No paintings by Michelangelo are likely to
appear on the market and very few of his drawings remain in private hands.
Any rich museum, such as the Getty in Malibu, California, might regard this
as a last chance to acquire a work by one of the greatest of artists.
The drawing has an excellent provenance. It was apparently sold in the 1830s
for 250 guineas. It comes from a British family but the government is
unlikely to prevent it leaving the country.
The miniature is by Hans Holbein, a double portrait of the Tudor statesman
Thomas Cromwell in a single frame. In 1932 it sold at Christie's for Pounds
2,000. This time a price of about Pounds 500,000 is expected.
</TEXT>
